    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What Are Hierarchical Task Networks?"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Hierarchical Task Networks (HTN) are a planning formalism where tasks are decomposed top-down through a hierarchy. A "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "compound task"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is abstract and cannot be executed directly \u2014 it must be decomposed into subtasks via a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "method"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". A "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "primitive task"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " maps directly to an executable action. Planning succeeds when every compound task has been recursively decomposed down to a sequence of primitive tasks."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "HTN decomposition: compound task prepare-report decomposes via method standard-report into compound task analyse and two primitive tasks; analyse further decomposes into two primitives",
          "title": "HTN decomposition tree: compound tasks, methods, and primitive tasks"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "HTN planners encode expert knowledge in methods: 'to achieve X, do these subtasks in this order, under these conditions.' This domain knowledge makes HTN planning dramatically more efficient than STRIPS search for structured domains."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Core Data Structures"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "An HTN domain contains two kinds of objects: "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "PrimitiveTask"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (directly executable, with preconditions and effects) and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Method"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (a decomposition rule for a compound task, with its own preconditions and an ordered subtask list):"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom typing import Callable\n\n@dataclass\nclass PrimitiveTask:\n    \"\"\"Directly executable action.\"\"\"\n    name: str\n    preconditions: set[str]\n    effects: set[str]       # add effects (delete handled separately if needed)\n    execute: Callable       # the actual tool/function to run\n\n@dataclass\nclass Method:\n    \"\"\"Decomposition rule for a compound task.\"\"\"\n    name: str\n    task_name: str          # the compound task this applies to\n    preconditions: set[str] # must hold in current state for this method to apply\n    subtasks: list          # ordered list of task names (compound or primitive)\n\n@dataclass\nclass HTNDomain:\n    \"\"\"Complete HTN domain: primitives + methods.\"\"\"\n    primitives: dict[str, PrimitiveTask] = field(default_factory=dict)\n    methods:    dict[str, list[Method]]  = field(default_factory=dict)\n\n    def add_primitive(self, task: PrimitiveTask) -> None:\n        self.primitives[task.name] = task\n\n    def add_method(self, method: Method) -> None:\n        self.methods.setdefault(method.task_name, []).append(method)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The HTN Planning Algorithm"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "HTN planning is a depth-first search over task decompositions. For each task in the current task list: if it is primitive, apply it (update state); if it is compound, try each applicable method in order and recurse on the method's subtask list:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def htn_plan(\n    tasks: list[str],\n    state: set[str],\n    domain: HTNDomain,\n) -> list[str] | None:\n    \"\"\"Total-order HTN planner: depth-first decomposition.\n\n    Returns the ordered list of primitive task names to execute,\n    or None if no plan was found.\n    \"\"\"\n    if not tasks:\n        return []  # empty plan succeeds trivially\n\n    task_name, *remaining = tasks\n\n    # Case 1: primitive task\n    if task_name in domain.primitives:\n        primitive = domain.primitives[task_name]\n        if not primitive.preconditions <= state:\n            return None  # preconditions not met\n        new_state = state | primitive.effects\n        rest_plan = htn_plan(remaining, new_state, domain)\n        if rest_plan is not None:\n            return [task_name] + rest_plan\n        return None\n\n    # Case 2: compound task \u2014 try each applicable method\n    for method in domain.methods.get(task_name, []):\n        if method.preconditions <= state:  # method is applicable\n            new_tasks = method.subtasks + remaining\n            plan = htn_plan(new_tasks, state, domain)\n            if plan is not None:\n                return plan  # first successful decomposition wins\n\n    return None  # no applicable method or decomposition failed"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The algorithm is "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "sound"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ": every returned plan satisfies all primitive preconditions in execution order. It is "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "complete"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " when the method set covers all reachable compound tasks. The depth-first strategy (first applicable method wins) is not optimal but is fast."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LLM-Driven Decomposition"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When a compound task has no registered methods \u2014 or when the domain is too open-ended to enumerate methods in advance \u2014 the LLM can select or generate a decomposition. The LLM acts as a dynamic method selector:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "HTN_DECOMPOSE_PROMPT = \"\"\"\nYou are an HTN (Hierarchical Task Network) planner.\nGiven a high-level task and the current state, choose the most\nappropriate decomposition method and return the ordered subtasks.\n\nTask: {task}\nCurrent state facts: {state}\nAvailable methods for this task:\n{methods}\n\nReturn JSON:\n{{\n  \"method_chosen\": \"<method_name>\",\n  \"rationale\": \"<why this method fits>\",\n  \"subtasks\": [\"<subtask1>\", \"<subtask2>\", ...]\n}}\n\"\"\"\n\ndef llm_decompose(\n    task: str,\n    state: set[str],\n    available_methods: list[dict],\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Use the LLM to select a decomposition method for a compound task.\"\"\"\n    methods_text = \"\\n\".join(\n        f\"- {m['name']}: {m['description']} (requires: {m.get('preconditions', [])})\" \n        for m in available_methods\n    )\n    response = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        max_tokens=512,\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": HTN_DECOMPOSE_PROMPT.format(\n            task=task,\n            state=\", \".join(sorted(state)),\n            methods=methods_text,\n        )}],\n    )\n    return json.loads(response.content[0].text)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Hybrid HTN: Registered Methods + LLM Fallback"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The most robust architecture registers methods for well-understood compound tasks (guaranteeing fast, correct decomposition) and falls back to the LLM for novel tasks. This hybrid approach gives HTN's structure for known domains while retaining flexibility:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def htn_plan_with_llm(\n    task: str,\n    state: set[str],\n    domain: HTNDomain,\n    max_depth: int = 8,\n    depth: int = 0,\n) -> list[str] | None:\n    \"\"\"HTN planning where compound task decomposition uses the LLM.\n\n    Primitive tasks still execute directly against the domain.\n    Compound tasks without registered methods are decomposed by the LLM.\n    \"\"\"\n    if depth > max_depth:\n        return None  # depth limit reached\n\n    # Primitive task: execute directly\n    if task in domain.primitives:\n        primitive = domain.primitives[task]\n        if primitive.preconditions <= state:\n            return [task]\n        return None\n\n    # Compound task with registered methods: try them in order\n    if task in domain.methods:\n        for method in domain.methods[task]:\n            if method.preconditions <= state:\n                subtask_plans = []\n                current_state = state.copy()\n                for subtask in method.subtasks:\n                    plan = htn_plan_with_llm(\n                        subtask, current_state, domain, max_depth, depth + 1\n                    )\n                    if plan is None:\n                        break\n                    subtask_plans.extend(plan)\n                    # Update state with primitive effects\n                    for p in plan:\n                        if p in domain.primitives:\n                            current_state |= domain.primitives[p].effects\n                else:\n                    return subtask_plans\n\n    # Compound task without registered methods: ask the LLM\n    decomp = llm_decompose(\n        task, state,\n        available_methods=[{\"name\": \"llm-generated\", \"description\": \"Generate subtasks for this task\"}]\n    )\n    all_plans = []\n    current_state = state.copy()\n    for subtask in decomp[\"subtasks\"]:\n        plan = htn_plan_with_llm(subtask, current_state, domain, max_depth, depth + 1)\n        if plan is None:\n            return None\n        all_plans.extend(plan)\n        for p in plan:\n            if p in domain.primitives:\n                current_state |= domain.primitives[p].effects\n    return all_plans"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Complete Example"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A file-report domain with four primitive tasks and two compound tasks, solved via the pure symbolic HTN planner:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Example: file-report domain\nimport anthropic\nimport json\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\ndomain = HTNDomain()\n\n# Primitives\ndomain.add_primitive(PrimitiveTask(\n    name=\"load-data\",\n    preconditions=set(),\n    effects={\"data-loaded\"},\n    execute=lambda: print(\"Loading data...\"),\n))\ndomain.add_primitive(PrimitiveTask(\n    name=\"compute-stats\",\n    preconditions={\"data-loaded\"},\n    effects={\"stats-ready\"},\n    execute=lambda: print(\"Computing stats...\"),\n))\ndomain.add_primitive(PrimitiveTask(\n    name=\"write-file\",\n    preconditions={\"stats-ready\"},\n    effects={\"file-written\"},\n    execute=lambda: print(\"Writing report file...\"),\n))\ndomain.add_primitive(PrimitiveTask(\n    name=\"send-email\",\n    preconditions={\"file-written\"},\n    effects={\"email-sent\"},\n    execute=lambda: print(\"Sending email...\"),\n))\n\n# Methods\ndomain.add_method(Method(\n    name=\"analyse-standard\",\n    task_name=\"analyse\",\n    preconditions=set(),\n    subtasks=[\"load-data\", \"compute-stats\"],\n))\ndomain.add_method(Method(\n    name=\"prepare-report-full\",\n    task_name=\"prepare-report\",\n    preconditions=set(),\n    subtasks=[\"analyse\", \"write-file\", \"send-email\"],\n))\n\nplan = htn_plan([\"prepare-report\"], set(), domain)\nprint(\"Plan:\", plan)\n# Plan: [\"load-data\", \"compute-stats\", \"write-file\", \"send-email\"]"
          }
        ]
      },
