      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "HTN Concepts in LLM Agents"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Compound task recognition:"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " identify which parts of a goal are composite (require multiple sub-steps) vs atomic (single tool call). Prompt the LLM to label each subtask as compound or primitive before planning."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Method library:"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " maintain a library of known decomposition patterns (e.g., 'to write a report: research \u2192 outline \u2192 draft \u2192 review'). Match incoming tasks against this library before asking the LLM to decompose."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Precondition checking at method selection:"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " before committing to a decomposition, verify that the method's preconditions hold in the current state. This prevents a decomposition that looks correct structurally but fails at execution."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Partial-order vs total-order:"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " total-order HTN (used above) fixes the subtask sequence. Partial-order HTN allows subtasks to be unordered, enabling parallelism. For LLM agents, add a "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "depends_on"
                  },
                  {
